						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>My guild hasn't had a problem with having too many bards.&nbsp; We routinely have 3-4 bards that are kept busy with whatever.&nbsp; Our rogues, wizards, etc. still beg for the extra attack from SoE, attack from Mastruq, or overhaste/dmg from Trusik.&nbsp; We generally have 1 or 2 bards doing AE resists (the two with max percussion mod)&nbsp;if they are needed--resists hard cap but with the massive resist adjustment on some AE's you can never have too many resists and overlapping effect from multiple bards ensures missed notes won't let resists fall.&nbsp; Thus in AE fights I end up twisting AE resists, Psalm of Veeshan, and one other depending on the group.&nbsp; Any group with a bard benefits from Psalm of Veeshan in an AE fight, so it isn't like the bard is being particularly wasted by being there.&nbsp; My resists end up significantly over 500 with psalm, but the AE's still hit partially and sometimes fully so the extra resists are definately helping out.&nbsp; In non AE fights I'll tailor songs to the group, but in general I'm not feeling inadequate or anything.&nbsp; Occasionally I'll start twisting some chants in with a twist, especially with unresistable AE's--full 4 twist chants with SoE haste and EoE/SoE equipped I hit ~200-205 DPS on boss fights.&nbsp; That's not exactly tremendous DPS compared to nukers and melee DD but it sure isn't bad considering the chants are helping the casters land for full more often <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But having a little more melee DPS wouldn't hurt, I'm just not agreeing that more than two bards are useless to have around for higher end GoD content.&nbsp; This may change past Inktu'ta, but we're certainly utilizing more than 2 bards without anyone whining.&nbsp; That's with monks pulling as well (i.e. none of the 4 bards are pulling for whatever reason).&nbsp; You have to remember that the majority of the songs we're using are manaless and stack with all other effects, so it's hard to ask for upgrades given just that fact.</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
