<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Tremelo-1018-Prexus wrote:<BR>
<DIV>1. Pretty much everyone is max resists (or unresistable AE's) <BR><FONT color=#66ff00>If 300vsall is max resists, then yes.. but not everyone has that. Havent yet seen a guild that would retain it's hard core of 54 people at maximum equipped pwnage)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. Melees have max attack (warmarch should add +250 attack to be effective<FONT color=#66ff00>)<BR>Even so if the melee's have max attack, i STILL get begged by rogues/monks/rangers to PLEASE click my SotE and play Warmarch.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. Warriors have 2800 AC (niv's harmonic should have +300 AC to be effective)</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>Fully agree with you here. The difference Niv's makes is just too small to be that much effective, especially with mobs being made for us being level 70. Tho, where you picked the number 2800 AC is beyond me.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>*eqrankings show top10 Warriors serverwide having more than 2600 AC unbuffed. So, not all warriors have 2800 AC. Let's not generalize.*</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Casters have very good focus items (echo is relatively much less significant)</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>I wouldnt call Echo "much less significant" mainly because it stacks with focus items. 45% to Nukes + having Echo running, still gets out the best DPS out of a nuke class. Then there's the overhaste it provides. Rogues absolutely thrive at being overhasted.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5. Casters have FT15 or very close to it (mana song is relatively much less effective)</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>Is that why everyone demands we keep it running at all times then, on all raids? Because it's less effective? Oh puhleeeeeze.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6. Everyone has at least 8K hps (regen on marr is much less effective)</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>I'm not playing Chorus of Marr because of HP regen in the first place. The HP regen of Marr doesnt matter much anywhere.. hp/tick that you can squeeze out of it with max mod, it still doesn't overcome the difficulty of the environment where the damage received by overall raid/group is much much greater.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>7. Mobs do massive amount of damage per hit (DS is much less effective)</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>Since GoD was returned, that is somewhat questionable. GoD mobs no longer hit for full dmg as often, so having 200+ DS on the main tank is still effective. Especially if mob is unslowable. For god's sake Tremelo, 200DS is about as much replacement to bard dps as it is helping squeeze in as much dmg as possible.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>8. Warriors (except for trolls &amp; ogres) are maxxed charisma</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>FYI, Trolls &amp; Ogres have maxxed charisma too.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We can pre-mez on pulls, but you get to something like ikkinz 4, 2nd to last boss and AE mez is really the tool.&nbsp; We can still pull and then beg a cleric for divine rez if we die (yes, it happens).</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>This looks like a que on trying to fill the full role of an enchanter. Sorry wont work. Enchanters are masters of mezzes, that's why THEY get Mesmerization mastery &amp; we dont. Besides.. We've done that encounter with 3 bards &amp; 2 chanters, without AE mez. It's completely doable, all you have to do is have it cleared out who does what when and where.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2 bards are good max for the raid.&nbsp; 1 to be on the pull team.&nbsp; 1 to play mana song.&nbsp; Anything else is just pretty insignificant.&nbsp; It would be nice if we were 85-100% of warrior damage.&nbsp; Since we can't off-tank, at least it would give us more desirability.</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>I strongly disagree with you here. We have regulary 4-5 bards/raid and we've never seen it as redundant. We provide a lot of options for any group to survive out there in the encounters. Why? Because we make use do with what we have. Certain encounters in GoD are such that ALL classes meet a time when their presence in greater numbers on raids, is redundant.. (Cursebearers in Inktu`ta, need non-mana dps mostly and 3 click rezzers)</FONT></DIV><BR>
