		<tr>
			
			<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>

						
							
				
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=40719' class="auth_text" style="font-weight:bold;"><span style='color:#336600;'>Booperbustle</span></a>
				<br>

								
				<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
									Journeyman
								<br>
									Posts: 37<br>
													Registered: 06-03-2004
				
				</span>
									<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=40719'>			
	
			<img src="/eq/i/icons/Races/gnome.jpg" border=0 alt="">
		</a><br>

				<span class=text_smallest>
								Server: Solusek Ro<br>
								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 94 times<br>
									</span>

									
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Breaking down what Tremelo is saying.&nbsp; I respect your opinion Tremelo, but I'm finding it very hard to agree with a lot of these points.&nbsp; It can't be *that* much different past Inktu'ta.&nbsp; If every bard in a raid is intuitive enough, they can be significant enough to tip the balance on any raid encounter.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. Pretty much everyone is max resists (or unresistable AE's) <BR>To put this into perspective, take Plane of Time's Terris Thule's AE, Quivering Nightmare.&nbsp; It is a -400 to Magic Resistance adjustment.&nbsp; So let's say you *do* have ~400 Magic Resistance without songs going.&nbsp; Psalms with maxed out singing mods (a lot of bards can't achieve the max in singing very easily)--your adjusted magic is 315.&nbsp; That's if you're in a bard group and they're playing Psalms.&nbsp; Sure you can add Guardian Rhythms (which I actually get requested to do by my group on that particular fight) to help pump up resists, but I still get nailed by that AE.&nbsp; Now, fast forward to GoD, and you have AE's with sick Prismatic/Chromatic resist adjustments just as bad as TT's single resist adjustment.&nbsp; I would say the raid would love to have a bard for every group in that sort of situation, especially when the AE's landing can be devastating to a raid.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. Melees have max attack (warmarch should add +250 attack to be effective)<FONT color=#66ff00><BR></FONT>I still get rogues, rangers, monks, and any other melee-based class begging me to load this song, click Songblade, and even occasionally use my Ikkinz horn to max out the mod.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. Warriors have 2800 AC (niv's harmonic should have +300 AC to be effective)</DIV>
<DIV>Like #2, every tank group I'm in the warriors complain when I *don't* load Niv's Harmonic.&nbsp; I end up having to explain to them Niv's has a small magic-rune component (10 magic-based, focused by singing)&nbsp;which renders it useless in fights where there is an AE or the mob in question has a hard-to-resist proc.&nbsp; Therefore I compromise by loading Guardian Rhythms, which does have an AC component but does not get torn off by procs/AE's.&nbsp; Niv's Harmonic could be +1000 AC and it would still have limited use in upper end GoD given that most bosses and trash mobs have some sort of proc that would dissipate the song in the first place.&nbsp; If you do convince them to up the AC given by the song, please tell them to think about removing the rune component as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Casters have very good focus items (echo is relatively much less significant)</DIV>
<DIV>Again, same as #2 and #3--if I have one wizard in a group I get pestered to sing Echo of the Trusik.&nbsp; Most do not use their special AA familiars and would prefer me to play this song in my lineup than not.&nbsp; The extra damage may seem insignificant, but it adds up over long fights in a group full of casters.&nbsp; If it is so insignificant, please convince the caster community we're being useless by singing it <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5. Casters have FT15 or very close to it (mana song is relatively much less effective)</DIV>
<DIV>Disagreeing.&nbsp; If I stop singing Marr casters start sending tells asking why it is not going in the background.&nbsp; The only qualm I have is not being able to sing it most of the time because of pullers getting nailed by it and me training the raid accidentally.&nbsp; I think I get more use out of Fading Memories in a day's time fading aggro from potential trains from this happening.&nbsp; Nonetheless, the rest of the EQ community likes to have Marr at all times (mana is mana), so it isn't useless and far from ineffective.&nbsp; Add on to this that more AE's are having a mana drain added and it does end up helping regardless.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6. Everyone has at least 8K hps (regen on marr is much less effective)</DIV>
<DIV>Agreeing with someone else--I'm not singing Marr for hp regen, but even I occasionally load my best lute when I'm not doing resists in AE fights to help with the healing.&nbsp; ~80-ish hp/tick spread across the entire raid may not seem like much, but it is adding to the healing.&nbsp; Given that most of the raid will have maxed out worn regen, the majority of the raid will have around 120-ish heal over time going during AE fights, which will make at least somewhat of a difference.&nbsp; Oh, and can't discount the extra mana/tick that it is adding as well.&nbsp; If they ever fix Marr and other effects that once regenerated stamina to regenerate endurance, I can see the melees desiring this song to be going as well (yes, they do run out of endurance due to AE drains, long fights, and chain clearing).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>7. Mobs do massive amount of damage per hit (DS is much less effective)</DIV>
<DIV>Most boss mobs I've run across up to Inktu'ta are either highly resistant (ie. almost impossible to slow) or unslowable.&nbsp; Having a 150+ DS on the tank during these encounters does a lot of manaless damage to a mob.&nbsp; It may not be as effective as 2 years ago when the DS was the #1 source of damage on a mob like Avatar of War, but it isn't far from the top even today.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>8. Warriors (except for trolls &amp; ogres) are maxxed charisma</DIV>
<DIV>I never get asked to play charisma song in the tank group--99% of all warriors I'm grouped with are maxed.&nbsp; But then again I never was asked to play charisma even when DI was used.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9. We can pre-mez on pulls, but you get to something like ikkinz 4, 2nd to last boss and AE mez is really the tool.&nbsp; We can still pull and then beg a cleric for divine rez if we die (yes, it happens).</DIV>
<DIV>If I stop pre-mezzing/pre-slowing pulls (especially when I'm pulling), it is very apparent when slowers and enchanters are dying.&nbsp; Bards backup mezzing is extremely useful (just ask the enchanters in my guild if they'd like me to stop helping).&nbsp; We may not have AE mez, but our mez is manaless and deadly efficient given that we can cast on the run and fade.&nbsp; Plus we have tons better mitigation over enchanters so we may actually live through a few hits on a resist, which gives the enchanters time to stick their superior mez.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10. 2 bards are good max for the raid.&nbsp; 1 to be on the pull team.&nbsp; 1 to play mana song.&nbsp; Anything else is just pretty insignificant.&nbsp; It would be nice if we were 85-100% of warrior damage.&nbsp; Since we can't off-tank, at least it would give us more desirability.</DIV>
<DIV>As stated above, my guild usually has 4 bards on a raid and we are kept very busy with our duties.&nbsp; Generally one or more of us pre-slow, pre-mez, debuff, mana song, do resists, operate in the tank group, pull (we will tag team some difficult pulls with one another and monks).&nbsp; Need I mention how significant it can be to have a bard playing psalms in each group during AE fights?&nbsp; If nothing else load up 4 chants and melee--that can fetch you around 200+ DPS with decent worn percussion mod and Time+ weapons as well as offer a great amount of debuffs to the raid.&nbsp; I know, I've achieved that.<BR></DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>-<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=994568>Sedenten Grey</a><br>Maestro of Firiona Vie<br><a href=http://www.fnfguild.com>Fire and Fury</a><br><br>-<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062>Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><br>Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro<br><a href=http://www.furiouspantaloons.org>Furious Pantaloons</a>
							</div>
																
